<h3>Install</h3>
<p>Please backup WHMCS and MailWizz before proceeding, including all files and databases</p>
<p>1. Install the WHMCS Connector Extension into MailWizz</p>
<ul>
  <li>Log in to the backend of your MailWizz EMA and navigate to the Extensions menu</li>
  <li>Hit the upload button and select the whmcs-connector.zip file contained in this package and upload it</li>
  <li>Enable the extension then click on it's title to go to the extension settings </li>
  <li>Configure the settings how you want them and copy the Hostname and Access Hash, you will need to enter these into WHMCS </li>
</ul>
<p>2. Install and configure the WHMCS Module
</p>
<ul>
  <li>FTP the modules folder to your WHMCS installation</li>
  <li>Log into WHMCS and navigate to Setup -&gt; Products/Services -&gt; Servers</li>
  <li>Click 'Add New Server' and for Module choose MailWizz</li>
  <li>Copy and paste the Hostname and Access Hash from the WHMCS Connector Extension settings screen in MailWizz. Leave the Username and Password empty. </li>
</ul>
<p>3. Configure some products in WHMCS
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Log into WHMCS and navigate to Setup -&gt; Products/Services -&gt; Products/Services</li>
  <li> Click 'Create a New Product'.</li>
  <li>Set the Product Type to Other and the Module to MailWizz</li>
  <li>On the next screen, on the Module Settings tab choose the Customer Group from MailWizz</li>
</ul>
